Businessman Jabu Mabuza has been given several vital roles at under-pressure power utility Eskom. On Monday afternoon, public enterprises minister Pravin Gordhan confirmed that Mabuza had been appointed as: The latter  came as a result of Phakamani Hadebe's resignation, which comes into effect from Thursday. "Within the three-month period during which Mr Mabuza will be the executive chairman and acting CEO, the Eskom board will conclude the process of identifying a suitable candidate to become the next Eskom GCEO," said Gordhan in a statement.